window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>From <i>NY Times</i> and <i>USA Today</i> best-selling author Jana DeLeon.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>Mallory Devereaux is known throughout the town of Royal Flush, Louisiana, as a walking disaster, and her luck just got worse. She needs to raise $10,000 in one week to keep the IRS from seizing her adoptive father’s business, where she works as the demolition foreman.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>When the opportunity to cool cards at her uncle’s casino comes up, Mallory hopes her luck is changing. But when she realizes her uncle has assembled a tournament of criminals, she wonders what she’s stepped in the middle of.</p>"; 
